    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Calls all other methods in order to create a MST using an implementation of Prim's algorithm. This will print an error message if no filename and exit(-1).
        Parameters:
        args - a string holding command line arugments. In this case the argument is the file name and is accesible by using args[0].

      • readFile

        public static void readFile(java.lang.String file)
        Reads the data from the file passed in from the command line. This method uses a BufferedReader to gather data line by line. The line is then split based on whitespace and stored into a variable called tokens. Each token is then passed into methods accordinly. Also, all vertices from the graph are put into a set for later use.
        Parameters:
        file - the name of the file which was passed into the command line.

      • printGraph

        public static void printGraph(Node n)
        Prints all edges of the graph in the following format: (vertex1, vertex2, weight) ...

      • printMST

        public static void printMST()
        Prints the edges inlcuded in the MST after Prim's has been run in the following format: (vertex1, vertex2, weight) ...

      • printLine

        public static void printLine()
        Prints a horizontal line used for formatting purposes only. Seperates the graph from the MST during output.
